name: Warung meduwi asri
address: Banjar Utu, Subak Umedui, J47V+MMP, Jatiluwih, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1: Such a little hidden secret on the white trekking route. The owners are such kind people and I had a really nice and informative chat via google translator. They grow and sell home-grown avocados, cocoa, coffee and even vanilla and in their garden. Highly recommended to stop by!
review 2: If you are taking the White trekking route, would really recommend stopping by at "Warung Meduwi Asri". The husband-and-wife owner are really friendly, and would be more than glad to show you around their garden. You can purchase some coconuts from them as well, which will be freshly picked from a nearby tree.
